+# Sphinx actionability addendum (per Soliton bench/crb/sphinx-actionability-spec.md).
+# When --sphinx is set, the judge returns the same match decision PLUS an actionability
+# rating distinguishing "wrong" findings from "correct but vague / non-actionable" findings.
+JUDGE_PROMPT_SPHINX = """You are evaluating AI code review tools.
+Determine (1) if the candidate issue matches the golden (expected) comment, and
+(2) whether the candidate is ACTIONABLE — i.e., specific enough that a developer
+would actually change code in response to it.
+
+Golden Comment (the issue we're looking for):
+{golden_comment}
+
+Candidate Issue (from the tool's review):
+{candidate}
+
+Match instructions (same as standard judge):
+- Determine if the candidate identifies the SAME underlying issue as the golden comment
+- Accept semantic matches - different wording is fine if it's the same problem
+- Focus on whether they point to the same bug, concern, or code issue
+
+Actionability instructions (Sphinx-style; applies whether or not match is true):
+Mark actionability="actionable" when ALL of:
+  - The finding names a specific code change (e.g., "replace X with Y", "add null check at line N")
+  - The change has a concrete impact (fixes a bug, prevents a regression, improves a measurable quality)
+  - A typical reviewer would request this change before merge
+Mark actionability="non_actionable" when ANY of:
+  - The finding says "consider X" / "you might want to" without a concrete change
+  - The finding is style-only (formatting, naming, ordering) without citing a specific style-guide rule
+  - The suggestion is overly broad, speculative, or would not pass code review
+  - The fix would not change observable behavior or maintainability
+  - The finding is correct but redundant with documentation already visible at the change site
+Mark actionability="uncertain" only when the candidate is too truncated or ambiguous to judge.
+
+Respond with ONLY a JSON object:
+{{"reasoning": "brief explanation of match decision", "match": true/false, "confidence": 0.0-1.0, "actionability": "actionable"|"non_actionable"|"uncertain", "actionability_reason": "1-sentence reason"}}"""
+
